<subSubSection id="EA8E6556D505FF84FCE56E43FDF9FE5F" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="34" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" type="description">
<paragraph id="A22B36DDD505FF82FCE56E43FB7CFC9E" blockId="3.[811,1457,343,2028]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">
The protologue of 
<taxonomicName id="65944D5ED505FF82FC206E43FC89FE1F" authority="(Desfontaines 1798: 52)" baseAuthorityName="Desfontaines" baseAuthorityPageNumber="52" baseAuthorityYear="1798" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Anarrhinum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fruticosum">
<emphasis id="90E0EACFD505FF82FC206E43FB0DFE3F" box="[1000,1238,375,401]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">Anarrhinum fruticosum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="C6054B2CD505FF82FB2D6E43FC91FE1F" author="DESFONTAINES R. L." pageId="3" pageNumber="32" refId="ref2948" refString="DESFONTAINES R. L. 1798. - Flora atlantica, sive historia plantarum, quae in atlante, agro tunetano et algeriensi crescent. Tomus primus. L. G. Desgranges, Paris, 444 p. https: // bibdigital. rjb. csic. es / idviewer / 10277 / 488" type="book" year="1798">Desfontaines 1798: 52</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
consists of a short diagnosis (“ 
<taxonomicName id="65944D5ED505FF82FB6E6EA3FAB2FE1F" box="[1190,1385,407,433]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Anarrhinum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">ANARRHINUM</taxonomicName>
frutescens; ramis virgatis, filiformibus; foliis perennantibus; imis spathulatis; racemis interruptis; corollis ecaudatis”), a detailed description (in Latin), and several geographical provenances (“HABITAT in Atlante prope Tlemsen [currently 
<collectingRegion id="6050F83FD505FF82FA876D22FA74FD9E" box="[1359,1455,534,560]" country="Algeria" name="Tlemcen" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">Tlemcen</collectingRegion>
in western 
<collectingCountry id="DA83764DD505FF82FC6A6D01FC2FFDFE" box="[930,1012,565,592]" name="Algeria" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">Algeria</collectingCountry>
], Mascar [central 
<collectingCountry id="DA83764DD505FF82FB786D01FB24FDFE" box="[1200,1279,565,592]" name="Algeria" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">Algeria</collectingCountry>
] et Cafsam [currently 
<collectingRegion id="6050F83FD505FF82FCBB6D62FC6BFDDE" box="[883,944,598,624]" country="Tunisia" name="Gafsa" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">Gafsa</collectingRegion>
in northern 
<collectingCountry id="DA83764DD505FF82FBF56D61FB4EFDDE" box="[1085,1173,597,624]" name="Tunisia" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">Tunisia</collectingCountry>
]”). Desfontaines (l.c.) also published an excellent illustration (“Tab. 142”) that is part of the original material and therefore considered for the typification purpose. Tab. 142 illustrates a stem with leaves, flowers (with several details) and fruits (
<figureCitation id="3AAF2A58D505FF82FB4F6DE1FB1EFD5E" box="[1159,1221,725,752]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="4.[401,412,2008,2025]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,215,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-20@4.[132,1455,215,1916]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIG. 1. — Lectotype of Anarrhinum fruticosum Desf., illustration in Desfontaines (1798: pl. 142)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4555430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4555430/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). This morphology is consistent with the current concept of the species (
<bibRefCitation id="C6054B2CD505FF82FAF26DC1FCBDFC81" author="FERNANDES R. B." pageId="3" pageNumber="32" pagination="221" refId="ref3087" refString="FERNANDES R. B. 1972. - Anarrhinum Desf., in TUTIN T. G., HEYWOOD V. H., BURGES N. A., VALENTINE D. H., WALTERS S. M. &amp; WEBB D. A. (eds), Flora Europaea. Vol. 3. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge: 220, 221." type="journal article" year="1972">Fernandes, 1972</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="C6054B2CD505FF82FCBB6C21FBDFFC81" author="SUTTON D. A." box="[883,1028,789,815]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" refId="ref3511" refString="SUTTON D. A. 1988. - A Revision of the Tribe Antirrhineae. British Museum (Natural History), London, 550 p." type="book" year="1988">Sutton, 1988</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="C6054B2CD505FF82FBC76C21FB4CFC81" author="AMICH F." box="[1039,1175,789,815]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" refId="ref2799" refString="AMICH F. 2009. - Anarrhinum Desf., in CASTROVIEJO S., HER- RERO A., BENEDI C., RICO E. &amp; GUEMES J. (eds), Flora Iberica. Vol. 13. Real Jardin Botanico, Csic, Madrid: 224 - 231." type="book" year="2009">Amich 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A22B36DDD505FF82FC8B6C01FBDCFB00" blockId="3.[811,1457,343,2028]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">
<bibRefCitation id="C6054B2CD505FF82FC8B6C01FBC2FCFE" author="SUTTON D. A." box="[835,1049,821,848]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" refId="ref3511" refString="SUTTON D. A. 1988. - A Revision of the Tribe Antirrhineae. British Museum (Natural History), London, 550 p." type="book" year="1988">Sutton (1988: 255)</bibRefCitation>
indicated: “Type: 
<collectingCountry id="DA83764DD505FF82FB2E6C01FAEDFCE1" box="[1254,1334,821,847]" name="Algeria" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">Algeria</collectingCountry>
: in Atlante prope Tlemsen [
<collectingRegion id="6050F83FD505FF82FC286C60FB9EFCC1" box="[992,1093,852,879]" country="Algeria" name="Tlemcen" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">Tlemcen</collectingRegion>
] 
<emphasis id="90E0EACFD505FF82FB9B6C61FADAFCC1" box="[1107,1281,853,879]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">Desfontaines s.n.</emphasis>
(syn. P-Desf.?); Mascar 
<emphasis id="90E0EACFD505FF82FC4E6C41FBE1FC21" box="[902,1082,885,911]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">Desfontaines s.n.</emphasis>
(syn. P-Desf.?). 
<collectingCountry id="DA83764DD505FF82FB316C41FA94FC21" box="[1273,1359,885,911]" name="Tunisia" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">Tunisia</collectingCountry>
: Cafsam [
<collectingRegion id="6050F83FD505FF82FCFD6CA0FCACFC01" box="[821,887,916,943]" country="Tunisia" name="Gafsa" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">Gafsa</collectingRegion>
] syn. P- 
<emphasis id="90E0EACFD505FF82FC106CA1FB5DFC01" box="[984,1158,917,943]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">Desfontaines s.n.</emphasis>
(syn. P-Desf.?)”. However, this is not an effective 
<typeStatus id="7D2F887FD505FF82FBE16C81FB50FC61" box="[1065,1163,949,975]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">lectotype</typeStatus>
designation, because three different “specimens” were mentioned as “type” (see Art. 8.1 of 
<emphasis id="90E0EACFD505FF82FC8F6CC1FCADFBA1" box="[839,886,1013,1039]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">ICN</emphasis>
). Furthermore, no specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="65944D5ED505FF82FB756CC0FA76FBA1" baseAuthorityName="Desfontaines" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[1213,1453,1012,1039]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Anarrhinum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fruticosum">
<emphasis id="90E0EACFD505FF82FB756CC0FA76FBA1" box="[1213,1453,1012,1039]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">Anarrhinum fruticosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected by Desfontaines and deposited at P was traced. In addition, note that 
<bibRefCitation id="C6054B2CD505FF82FC376B00FB0AFBE1" author="SUTTON D. A." box="[1023,1233,1076,1103]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" refId="ref3511" refString="SUTTON D. A. 1988. - A Revision of the Tribe Antirrhineae. British Museum (Natural History), London, 550 p." type="book" year="1988">Sutton (1988: 255)</bibRefCitation>
indicated this material with a question mark, and he also mentioned “I have not been able to examine Desfontaines material at Paris yet to make the selection”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A22B36DDD505FF82FC8B6B80FBE2FAC0" blockId="3.[811,1457,343,2028]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">
René Louiche Desfontaines (1750-1833) was a French botanist, professor at the Jardin des Plantes in Paris. The personal herbarium of this author is now preserved at many herbaria, i.e. BM, C, CGE, FI (acquired via Webb) LIV, MPU, P (incl. PC, P-DESF, P-JU and P-LA) (see 
<bibRefCitation id="C6054B2CD505FF82FA806A07FC2FFAC3" author="STAFLEU F. A. &amp; COWAN R. S." pageId="3" pageNumber="32" refId="ref3460" refString="STAFLEU F. A. &amp; COWAN R. S. 1976. - Taxonomic Literature: A Selective Guide to Botanical Publications and Collections with Dates, Commentaries and Types. ed. 2, Vol. 1. Bohn, Scheltema &amp; Holkema, Utrecht, 1136 p." type="book" year="1976">Stafleu &amp; Cowan 1976: 627</bibRefCitation>
, 628).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A22B36DDD505FF82FC8B6A40FB6BF942" blockId="3.[811,1457,343,2028]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">
<materialsCitation id="12FC3C80D505FF82FC8B6A40FB6BF942" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3041291301" collectionCode="MPU" collectorName="We" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" specimenCode="MPU020302" specimenCount="1">
<collectorName id="0F61530BD505FF82FC8B6A40FCBCFA20" box="[835,871,1396,1422]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">We</collectorName>
have found a herbarium sheet of 
<taxonomicName id="65944D5ED505FF82FB196A47FC8BFA03" baseAuthorityName="Desfontaines" baseAuthorityYear="1798" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Anarrhinum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fruticosum">
<emphasis id="90E0EACFD505FF82FB196A47FC8BFA03" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">Anarrhinum fruticosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at 
<collectionCode id="C485AE18D505FF82FCBE6AA0FC6FFA00" box="[886,948,1428,1454]" country="France" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15519" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15519" name="Université Montpellier 2" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" type="Herbarium">MPU</collectionCode>
(barcode 
<specimenCode id="F2329EA6D505FF82FBED6AA7FB64FA03" box="[1061,1215,1427,1453]" collectionCode="MPU" country="France" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15519" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15519" name="Université Montpellier 2" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" type="Herbarium">MPU020302</specimenCode>
). The sheet bears two fragments with leaves, flowers and fruits, and the following label: “ 
<taxonomicName id="65944D5ED505FF82FCBB6AE7FBABFA43" baseAuthorityName="Desfontaines" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[883,1136,1491,1517]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Anarrhinum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fruticosum">Anarrhinum fruticosum</taxonomicName>
/ ex herbario 
<collectorName id="0F61530BD505FF82FB346AE7FA73FA43" box="[1276,1448,1491,1517]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">D. Desfontaines</collectorName>
” [probably handwritten by Candolle] (image available at https://herbier.umontpellier.fr/zoomify/zoomify.php?fichier= 
<specimenCode id="F2329EA6D505FF82FC996907FC39F9E3" box="[849,994,1587,1613]" collectionCode="MPU" country="France" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15519" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15519" name="Université Montpellier 2" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" type="Herbarium">MPU020302</specimenCode>
). Unfortunately, the date of collection or the provenance of the specimen is not reported on the label of the sheet and, as a consequence, we cannot be sure that it has been collected before 1798. Therefore 
<specimenCode id="F2329EA6D505FF82FAD669A6FA6AF902" box="[1310,1457,1682,1708]" collectionCode="MPU" country="France" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15519" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15519" name="Université Montpellier 2" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" type="Herbarium">MPU020302</specimenCode>
cannot be treated as original material and is not eligible as 
<typeStatus id="7D2F887FD505FF82FCE669E6FC4BF942" box="[814,912,1746,1772]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="65944D5ED505FF82FC7A69E6FB72F942" baseAuthorityName="Desfontaines" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[946,1193,1746,1772]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Anarrhinum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fruticosum">
<emphasis id="90E0EACFD505FF82FC7A69E6FB72F942" box="[946,1193,1746,1772]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">Anarrhinum fruticosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A22B36DDD505FF84FC8B69C6FE93FE9C" blockId="3.[811,1457,343,2028]" lastBlockId="5.[132,777,215,497]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="34" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">
Another specimen was found at B (Willdenow Herbarium, barcode B-W11330-01-0, image available at https://www.jacq. org/detail.php?ID=940496). This specimen, a stem with leaves and flowers, is annotated by Willdenow as: “ 
<taxonomicName id="65944D5ED505FF82FAC26866FA76F8C5" baseAuthorityName="Desfontaines" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[1290,1453,1873,1900]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Anarrhinum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fruticosum">An. fruticosum</taxonomicName>
1” [at the top of the sheet] and “Desfontaines W” [at the bottom]. However, this material cannot be treated as original material of 
<taxonomicName id="65944D5ED505FF82FC636885FBE3F865" baseAuthorityName="Desfontaines" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[939,1080,1969,1995]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Anarrhinum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fruticosum">
<emphasis id="90E0EACFD505FF82FC636885FBE3F865" box="[939,1080,1969,1995]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">A. fruticosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because the date of collection and provenance of the specimen are not reported on the sheet. We have not found any specimen of this species collected by Desfontaines in any of the consulted herbaria (e.g., BM, C, CGE, FI, LIV, P).
</paragraph>
<caption id="F6EB6655D502FF85FE5968ECFB7FF847" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4555430" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4555430" box="[401,1188,2008,2025]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4555430/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="33" startId="4.[401,412,2008,2025]" targetBox="[132,1455,215,1916]" targetPageId="4">
